snippet.textDisplay: There have been plenty of great musicians in the obituaries over the past 18-24 months (prince, Bowie, petty, EW&F Maurice, Grant Hart, et al).   However, the passing of Neil hit me like nothing I expected.  I hurt on the inside. I had no interest in doing much last weekend when I heard, etc.   I think the delta here is that NP was such a sweet, committed, honest, smart, likeable, honorable work horse.  He was so humble yet so brilliant. And Rush, almost like a relative that came to live in your parents home to ride it out, were part of my “household” for over 30 years, it cannot be helped to deeply lament this extraordinary man, and the poignancy of no longer having him on earth.... He was a real gift.   Thank you for reading.  Love,

snippet.textDisplay:
WOW! I JUST learned of this 1/13/20 5am. Night owl on my way to bed just lookin at UT drumming vids for a minute like I do a lot. . Won’t get to sleep easily now. I didn’t even know he was sick. I actually had the privilege of meeting him many years ago by accident. I was checking out his kit before a show when I didn’t even know who he was. One of those right place right time deals. Actually I was just about to be escorted out of the restricted area I somehow slipped into when he came out and told security it was ok. He talked with me for about 15 minutes and I was very impressed by his regular guy easy goin personality. After I saw him perform that night I was amazed by his talent and a big fan since. A true ICON and one of the very best in the world. No doubt. MANY will miss this man! I do already. Such a loss to this world.
Thanx, Neil...for everything!
